						<div class="postbody">I'm working on an action game right now, pretty much exactly like Castlevania: Symphony of the Night. But the objects just have to check if they're colliding with the player, or the weapon. So I need to check for collision for two objects, basically. By organizing their coordinates from low to high, it shouldn't take THAT long, but I was just thinking maybe it could take less. But yeah, if I had EVERY object collide with each other, it would be a nightmare.
<br />
<br />EDIT:
<br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"> How many objects per screen are you talking about?</div>
